</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFEC3934EBD2C5D2FEB25870" blockId="66.[225,1436,737,838]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Otoliths of 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFEC3934EA56C5D1FDDF59CD" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1999" box="[359,544,737,763]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psettodidae" genus="Psettodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trapeziformis">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFEC3934EA56C5D1FDDF59CD" box="[359,544,737,763]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">P. trapeziformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be readily distinguished by their elliptic shape with about similar dorsal and ventral areas, a sulcus without colliculum and a nearly straight cauda with a very slightly downwards bent end.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
